{"title": "Weather Report Opening", "content": "\u2014 Opening words of The Big Kill by Mickey Spillane \"It was one of those nights when the sky came down and wrapped itself around the world.\"\n\nWeather Report Opening is when some of the first words in a story are a comment on the weather. Seen a lot in Literature, but also shows up in Film Noir detective stories when the narration begins \"The rain was making a jazz drumbeat against my office window when the dame with the case walked in...\", or something similar.\n\n\"It Was a Dark and Stormy Night\" is the best known example and, by now, a subtrope by itself. A Storm Is Coming is when this is employed as Ominous Foreshadowing.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeatherReportOpening", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/MickeySpillane", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/KOn", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheLongHalloween", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/SinCity", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekVoyager", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/KikisDeliveryService", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Amelie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ThrowMommaFromTheTrain", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/GroundhogDay", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/NineteenEightyFour", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheJungleBook", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Neuromancer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Neverwhere", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/NeilGaiman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Uglies", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/RaymondChandler", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ToKillAMockingbird", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JKRowling", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/AnnieOnMyMind", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheNameOfTheRose", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/AnEncounterAndAnOffer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/FritzLeiber", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/RayBradbury", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/WhoNeedsMen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Radiance", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/OurMissBrooks", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Dragnet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.ph